sprint: S06
track: B
task: B3
title: "feat(brands): brand landing TypeCards — equipment-type static imagery"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: medium
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("it's a little bit too much the same with just boxes with little
    hex tractors in them")
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("incorporating specific imagery and clearer grouping will create
    a more intuitive experience")
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]

impact: |
  Brand landing pages currently show TypeCard grids with a generic category icon
  (hex tractor silhouette) regardless of brand. Customers landing on a Ferris page
  see the same visual as the New Holland page. Distinctive imagery per equipment type
  communicates brand identity immediately and reduces bounce.

description: |
  TypeCard (`app/parts-diagrams/_components/type-card.tsx`) receives an equipment-type
  object. The hono brand-hub route returns `imageUrl: null` for all models today
  (schema slot reserved — no hero image column on `models` table yet).

  V2 pragmatic fix: static curated image map per equipment-type slug. This requires
  no DB schema change and no hono change.

  Approach:
  1. Create `lib/brand/equipment-type-images.ts`: a map of equipmentType slug →
     static image path (placed in `public/images/equipment-types/`).
     e.g. { "tractors": "/images/equipment-types/tractors.webp", "mowers": "..." }
     Source: OEM marketing images (same images Vova has for Figma reference).
  2. `TypeCard` accepts an optional `imageUrl` prop (already may have one — check).
     If not, add it: when imageUrl is set, render it as a bg-image or <Image>
     instead of the generic icon.
  3. Brand landing page (`app/parts/brand/[slug]/page.tsx`): when mapping types to
     TypeCards, inject `imageUrl` from the static map.
  4. For types with no static image: retain current generic icon (graceful degradation).

  Image sourcing: Vova has Figma reference with brand imagery. Denis to coordinate
  with Vova on which images to use. 4-6 images needed (Tractors, Mowers, Hay Tools,
  Commercial Mowers, Utility Vehicles, Attachments). Formats: WebP, 400×250px,
  optimized via Next.js <Image>.

scope:
  in:
    - `lib/brand/equipment-type-images.ts`: static slug→image map
    - TypeCard: render static image when available
    - `/public/images/equipment-types/`: 4-6 curated images (Vova provides sources)
    - Brand landing: inject static images into TypeCard props
    - Unit test: TypeCard renders <Image> when imageUrl prop provided
  out:
    - Per-brand images (V2 is per-equipment-type; per-brand is a follow-up)
    - Changes to hono imageUrl field (deferred — no models.hero_image column yet)
    - Changing the TypeCard component structure

invariants:
  - <Image> component from Next.js — not <img> tag
  - All images must have descriptive alt text
  - Static images in public/ — no CDN dependency for V2 launch
  - No hardcoded hex colors — use Moby DS tokens for overlays

acceptance:
  - Brand landing for Ferris: "Commercial Mowers" TypeCard shows a mower image
  - Brand landing for New Holland (existing): no regression — NH TypeCards still render
  - TypeCard with no static image matches: renders existing generic icon (no broken img)
  - Lighthouse perf: no LCP regression (images should be lazy-loaded below-fold;
    above-fold can have priority flag)

dep: none
output: lib/brand/equipment-type-images.ts + TypeCard update + public/images/
